  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pancetta lardons</strong> and cook for 3-4 mins or until golden and crispy</p>\r\n<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>pancetta</strong> to kitchen paper</p>\r\n<p>Reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip the <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> and chop them roughly, discarding the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dissolve 1/2&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[1]&nbsp;</span><strong>chicken stock cube</strong> in 150ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> and <strong>chopped&nbsp;rosemary </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min, stirring occasionally until beginning to colour</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the&nbsp;<strong>tortiglioni pasta&nbsp;</strong>to a pot of&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong>&nbsp;with a large pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook the&nbsp;<strong>tortiglioni&nbsp;</strong>for 10-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain the<strong>&nbsp;tortiglioni</strong>, reserving a large cup of the&nbsp;<strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>butternut squash</strong> is coloured, add a generous splash of <strong>water</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 10 min or until softened</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, grate the<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the butternut squash has softened, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and&nbsp;cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>\r\n<p>Mash half the <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> with a masher until smooth</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and give everything a good mix up&nbsp;until a sauce has formed</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained tortiglioni</strong> to the pan and mix until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta</p>\r\n<p>Tip: add a splash of the starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>\r\n<p>Add half the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and mix to combine &ndash; this is your <strong>butternut squash tortiglioni</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1436_-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>butternut squash tortiglioni</strong> topped with the <strong>crispy pancetta</strong> and <strong>remaining cheese</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and drizzle with some <strong>olive oil&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
